Script,PlayTopTricksSuit
window.currentPBSScenario = 'PlayTopTricksSuit';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Play_Top_Tricks_Suit';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for PlayTopTricksSuit');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'PlayTopTricksSuit',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge
auction-filter: Auction.....\n((1C +Pass +[23]C|1D +Pass +[23]D|1H +Pass +[234]H|1S +Pass +[234]S) +Pass\nPass +Pass|1[CDHS] +Pass +1[DHSN] +Pass\n2[CDHS] +Pass +Pass +Pass)
*/
##### Imported Script -- Predict Opening 1-Bid South #####
# 01/19/2026 -- Changed to use TP and separate ranges for C, D, and majors
# 03/30/2025 -- Changed to use gibNT

# GIB opens 1N w/15-17 HCP or 15-16 and a 5-card major
ntP = hcp(south) + shape(south,5xxx+x5xx)
nt1 = shape(south, any 5332+any 4432+any 4333) and hcp(south)>14 and ntP<18

# GIB does not open with 5422 and a 5-card major
# GIB does not open with 5422 and the strength to reverse
nt2 = shape(south, any 5422 -5xxx-x5xx-4xxx) and hcp(south)>14 and hcp(south)<17

gibNT = nt1 or nt2

## Calculate TP for South -- NOTE:  This uses different variable names than TP to avoid conflicts when both are used.
# Calculate South's Short-Suit Penalty Points
ssp = spades(south)<3 and hcp(south,spades)>0     ? 1 : 0
shp = hearts(south)<3 and hcp(south,hearts)>0     ? 1 : 0
sdp = diamonds(south)<3 and hcp(south,diamonds)>0 ? 1 : 0
scp = clubs(south)<3 and hcp(south,clubs)>0       ? 1 : 0

# Calculate South's Short-Suit Points
sv01 = shape(south, any 0xxx) ? 3 : 0
ss01 = shape(south, any 1xxx) ? 2 : 0 // allow for 2 singletons
ss02 = shape(south, any 11xx) ? 2 : 0
sd01 = shape(south, any 2xxx) ? 1 : 0 // allow for 3 doubletons
sd02 = shape(south, any 22xx) ? 1 : 0
sd03 = shape(south, any 222x) ? 1 : 0

# Calculate South's Total Points
sTP = hcp(south) + sv01+ss01+ss02+sd01+sd02+sd03 -ssp-shp-sdp-scp

# Calculate length points for South (lengthPoints)
lp1 = spades(south)>4 ? spades(south)-4 : 0
lp2 = hearts(south)>4 ? hearts(south)-4 : 0
lp3 = diamonds(south)>4 ? diamonds(south)-4 : 0
lp4 = clubs(south)>4 ? clubs(south)-4 : 0
lengthPoints = lp1 + lp2 + lp3 + lp4

# Define suit points for south (suitPoints)
suitPoints = hcp(south) + lengthPoints

TwoNtShape = shape(south, any 4333 +any 4432 +any 5332 +any 5422)

# Define ntPoint ranges
oneNT   = gibNT
twoNT   = TwoNtShape and hcp(south)>19 and hcp(south)<22

# Define Gambling 3N
g3Shape = shape(south,any 9xxx +any 8xxx +any 7xxx -any 4xxx -any 5xxx -any 6xxx)
threeNT = (top3(south,clubs)==3 and clubs(south)>6) or (top3(south,diamonds)==3 and diamonds(south)>6) and hcp(south)<12 and g3Shape

# Define Game Forcing 2C
case1 = hcp(south)>18 and sTP>21
case2 = hcp(south)>18 and sTP>19 and losers(south)<5 and (spades(south)>5 or hearts(south)>5)
case3 = hcp(south)>18 and sTP>19 and losers(south)<4 and (diamonds(south)>5 or clubs(south)>5)
gameForce2C = (case1 or case2 or case3)

### Predict South's opening BID
P1 = gameForce2C
P2 = P1 or threeNT or twoNT or oneNT

# Define quality and length lower limits for 10 HCP openers

q2of3 = (top3(south,spades)>1 or top3(south,hearts)>1) and controls(south)>3
lgt5  = (spades(south)>4 or hearts(south)>4) and shape(south,any 7xxx +any 64xx +any 55xx +any 1xxx+any 0xxx -any 8xxx -any 54xx) and sTP>(hcp(south) +2)

# Predict South's Opening suit
# What's the longest suit?
s = spades(south)
h = hearts(south)
d = diamonds(south)
c = clubs(south)

## GIB has different requirements for 1H/S, 1D, and 1C openings 
#Define range for 1 H/S
lS = s>4 and s>=h and s>=d and s>=c
lH = h>4 and h>s and h>=d and h>=c
lM = lS or lH

hsOK1 = lM and hcp(south)>11
hsOK2 = lM and hcp(south)>10 and sTP>12 and not hsOK1
hsOK3 = lM and hcp(south)>9  and lgt5 and q2of3 and not (hsOK1 or hsOK2)
hsRange = (hsOK1 or hsOK2 or hsOK3) and not P2

# Define 1D Range
dOK1 = hcp(south)>11 and (diamonds(south)>3 or shape(south, 4432))
dOK2 = hcp(south)>9  and sTP>12 and diamonds(south)>5 and not dOK1
dRange = (dOK1 or dOK2) and not P2

# Define 1C Range
cOK1 = hcp(south)>10 and sTP>12 and spades(south)==4
cOK2 = hcp(south)>9  and sTP>12 and clubs(south)>5 and not cOK1
cOK3 = hcp(south)>11 and clubs(south)>2            and not (cOK1 or cOK2)
cRange = (cOK1 or cOK2 or cOK3) and clubs(south)>2 and clubs(south)>diamonds(south) and not P2

oS = s>4 and s>=h and s>=d and s>=c and hsRange
oH = not oS and h>4 and h>=d and h>=c and hsRange
oD = not (oS or oH) and ((d>3 and d>=c) or c<3) and dRange
oC = not (oS or oH or oD) and cRange
openingSuit = (oS or oH or oD or oC)
oneSpade   = oS
oneHeart   = oH
oneDiamond = oD
oneClub    = oC

##### End of Imported Script -- Predict Opening 1-Bid #####
# Provides oS, oH, oD, oC, openingSuit for South.

# Opener — 12-14 HCP, 1-of-suit opening (not 1NT)
sHcp    = hcp(south) > 11 and hcp(south) < 15
sNotNT  = not (shape(south, any 4333 + any 4432 + any 5332) and hcp(south) > 14 and hcp(south) < 18)
sOpens  = openingSuit and sNotNT

### Imported script: topTricksSuitNS (NS Top Tricks for SUIT contracts)
//
// Computes NS top tricks assuming OPENER's suit is trump.
//
// Trump suit:
//   If NS's consecutive top-honor chain (AKQJT) is large enough to draw all
//   opponents' trumps without loss (chainTrump >= oppsTrumpLen), then trump
//   tricks = NS combined trump length (cross-ruff / length play takes all
//   of them). Otherwise trump tricks = chainTrump only — opps' high trumps
//   take the rest.
//
//   Examples:
//     11-card fit + AK   (chain 2, opps 2) → 11 trump tricks
//     10-card fit + AKQ  (chain 3, opps 3) → 10 trump tricks
//      9-card fit + AKQJ (chain 4, opps 4) →  9 trump tricks
//      8-card fit + AKQ  (chain 3, opps 5) →  3 trump tricks (lose 2)
//
// Side suits (non-trump):
//   +1 per side suit for first-round stop (NS holds the ace, or either
//      hand is void).
//   +1 per side suit for a second-round ruff: a void hand that still holds
//      4+ trumps takes a second ruff before running out.
//
// Total topTricksNS is capped at 13 (max tricks in a deal).
//
// Stopper rule:
//   Every suit must have a first-round stop (ace or void). If any side suit
//   is unstopped, opponents cash winners before declarer can — so scenarios
//   should also require `nsAllStopped`, not just a threshold on topTricksNS.
//
// Trump-suit caveat:
//   Uses opener's suit as trump (via oS/oH/oD/oC). For auctions where opener
//   raises responder (e.g., 1X-1Y-2Y) the actual trump is Y, and the trump
//   computation will be off. Acceptable for the dominant cases:
//     1X — Pass — 2X — all pass
//     1X — Pass — 3X — all pass
//     1X — Pass — 1Y — Pass — 2X — all pass
//
// Dependency: requires oS, oH, oD, oC defined first
// (e.g., via `#include "script/Predict-Opening-1-Bid"`)
//
// Exports: nsFirstS, nsFirstH, nsFirstD, nsFirstC,
//          nsRuffS,  nsRuffH,  nsRuffD,  nsRuffC,
//          nsAllStopped, trumpTricks, topTricksNS

// ---- Trump-suit length in each NS hand (opener's suit is trump) ----
sTrumps = oS ? spades(south) : (oH ? hearts(south) : (oD ? diamonds(south) : clubs(south)))
nTrumps = oS ? spades(north) : (oH ? hearts(north) : (oD ? diamonds(north) : clubs(north)))
nsTrumpLen   = sTrumps + nTrumps
oppsTrumpLen = 13 - nsTrumpLen

// ---- Has-honor in the trump suit (combined NS, picked by opener's suit) ----
hasAceTrump   = oS ? (hascard(south,AS) or hascard(north,AS))
              : (oH ? (hascard(south,AH) or hascard(north,AH))
              : (oD ? (hascard(south,AD) or hascard(north,AD))
              :       (hascard(south,AC) or hascard(north,AC))))
hasKingTrump  = oS ? (hascard(south,KS) or hascard(north,KS))
              : (oH ? (hascard(south,KH) or hascard(north,KH))
              : (oD ? (hascard(south,KD) or hascard(north,KD))
              :       (hascard(south,KC) or hascard(north,KC))))
hasQueenTrump = oS ? (hascard(south,QS) or hascard(north,QS))
              : (oH ? (hascard(south,QH) or hascard(north,QH))
              : (oD ? (hascard(south,QD) or hascard(north,QD))
              :       (hascard(south,QC) or hascard(north,QC))))
hasJackTrump  = oS ? (hascard(south,JS) or hascard(north,JS))
              : (oH ? (hascard(south,JH) or hascard(north,JH))
              : (oD ? (hascard(south,JD) or hascard(north,JD))
              :       (hascard(south,JC) or hascard(north,JC))))
hasTenTrump   = oS ? (hascard(south,TS) or hascard(north,TS))
              : (oH ? (hascard(south,TH) or hascard(north,TH))
              : (oD ? (hascard(south,TD) or hascard(north,TD))
              :       (hascard(south,TC) or hascard(north,TC))))

// ---- Trump chain: consecutive AKQJT held by NS ----
chainTrumpAfterJack  = hasTenTrump   ? 5 : 4
chainTrumpAfterQueen = hasJackTrump  ? chainTrumpAfterJack  : 3
chainTrumpAfterKing  = hasQueenTrump ? chainTrumpAfterQueen : 2
chainTrumpAfterAce   = hasKingTrump  ? chainTrumpAfterKing  : 1
chainTrump           = hasAceTrump   ? chainTrumpAfterAce   : 0

// ---- Trump tricks: full length when chain draws all opps, else chain ----
trumpTricks = chainTrump >= oppsTrumpLen ? nsTrumpLen : chainTrump

// ---- First-round stop per suit (ace, or void in either hand) ----
nsFirstS = hascard(south, AS) or hascard(north, AS) or spades(south)   == 0 or spades(north)   == 0
nsFirstH = hascard(south, AH) or hascard(north, AH) or hearts(south)   == 0 or hearts(north)   == 0
nsFirstD = hascard(south, AD) or hascard(north, AD) or diamonds(south) == 0 or diamonds(north) == 0
nsFirstC = hascard(south, AC) or hascard(north, AC) or clubs(south)    == 0 or clubs(north)    == 0

// ---- Second-round ruff: SIDE-suit void in a hand with 4+ trumps ----
nsRuffS = (not oS) and ((spades(south)  ==0 and sTrumps>3) or (spades(north)  ==0 and nTrumps>3))
nsRuffH = (not oH) and ((hearts(south)  ==0 and sTrumps>3) or (hearts(north)  ==0 and nTrumps>3))
nsRuffD = (not oD) and ((diamonds(south)==0 and sTrumps>3) or (diamonds(north)==0 and nTrumps>3))
nsRuffC = (not oC) and ((clubs(south)   ==0 and sTrumps>3) or (clubs(north)   ==0 and nTrumps>3))

// ---- Side-suit first-round stops (exclude trump — counted in trumpTricks) ----
sideStopS = (not oS) and nsFirstS
sideStopH = (not oH) and nsFirstH
sideStopD = (not oD) and nsFirstD
sideStopC = (not oC) and nsFirstC

// ---- Every suit first-round controlled ----
nsAllStopped = nsFirstS and nsFirstH and nsFirstD and nsFirstC

// ---- Top tricks total = trump tricks + side first-round + side ruffs (cap 13) ----
topTricksRaw = trumpTricks
             + sideStopS + sideStopH + sideStopD + sideStopC
             + nsRuffS   + nsRuffH   + nsRuffD   + nsRuffC

topTricksNS = topTricksRaw < 14 ? topTricksRaw : 13
# Provides topTricksNS and nsAllStopped. Trump = opener's suit.

# Responder support for opener's suit
# - Major opener (1H/1S): 3+ support; for 1H, no 4-card spades alternative
# - Minor opener (1C/1D): 4+ support and no 4-card major to bid first;
#                         for 1C, also no 4-card diamond response
nSupportS = oS and spades(north)   >= 3
nSupportH = oH and hearts(north)   >= 3 and spades(north) < 4
nSupportD = oD and diamonds(north) >= 4 and spades(north) < 4 and hearts(north) < 4
nSupportC = oC and clubs(north)    >= 4 and spades(north) < 4 and hearts(north) < 4 and diamonds(north) < 4
nHasFit   = nSupportS or nSupportH or nSupportD or nSupportC
nMajorFit = nSupportS or nSupportH

# Responder paths — each path targets a contract LEVEL with MATCHING top tricks
# 2X simple raise (6-9 HCP, any fit)      → 8 top tricks
# 3X limit raise  (10-12 HCP, any fit)    → 9 top tricks
# 4M game raise   (13-15 HCP, major fit)  → 10 top tricks
n2X = hcp(north) >  5 and hcp(north) < 10 and nHasFit   and topTricksNS ==  8
n3X = hcp(north) >  9 and hcp(north) < 13 and nHasFit   and topTricksNS ==  9
n4X = hcp(north) > 12 and hcp(north) < 16 and nMajorFit and topTricksNS == 10
nActs = n2X or n3X or n4X

# Quiet opponents — no overcalls or doubles
eHcp = hcp(east) < 11
wHcp = hcp(west) < 11

sOpens and sHcp and nActs and nsAllStopped and eHcp and wHcp

action printoneline,
average "South opens 1C   " 100 * oC,
average "South opens 1D   " 100 * oD,
average "South opens 1H   " 100 * oH,
average "South opens 1S   " 100 * oS,
average "Path 2X (6-9)    " 100 * n2X,
average "Path 3X (10-12)  " 100 * n3X,
average "Path 4M (13-15)  " 100 * n4X,
average "South HCP avg    "       hcp(south),
average "North HCP avg    "       hcp(north),
average "topTricksNS avg  "       topTricksNS,
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Top Tricks (Suit),\n\
--- Top Tricks — Suit Contract (beginner)\n\
The final contract is a suit partial or major-suit game. Top tricks\n\
are designed to MATCH the contract level:\n\
• 2X — simple raise — 8 top tricks (book 6 + 2)\n\
• 3X — limit raise — 9 top tricks\n\
• 4M — game in major — 10 top tricks\n\
\n\
Top tricks are first-round stops in every suit (ace or void) plus\n\
trump-suit tricks (combined NS trump length when the AKQJT chain is\n\
big enough to draw opps' trumps，else just the chain). A side-suit\n\
void in a hand with 4+ trumps adds a second-round ruff.\n\
\n\
Things to think about:\n\
• Count your top tricks BEFORE you do anything else.\n\
• If you already have your contract count，cash; don't risk a finesse\n\
  for an overtrick (matchpoints aside).\n\
• At 4M，drawing trumps and running length is the standard plan.\n\
\n\
Reference: https://www.bridgebum.com/counting.php\n\
%PlayTopTricksSuit%
